  the septuagint uses a number of terms to translate the 16 uses of nazir in the hebrew bible , such as " he who vowed " ( euxamenos εὐξαμένος ) or " he who was made holy " ( egiasmenos ἡγιασμένος ) etc .

in the bible : in the book of judges , his nazirite vows brought him great power but his passions brought his downfall

